[71.045795, "o", "EXPORT SCRIPT FIX SUMMARY\r\n=========================\r\n\r\nDate: $(date)\r\nScript: /home/user/admin/export_users.sh\r\n\r\nPROBLEMS IDENTIFIED:\r\n1. BUG 1: emails.dat is tab-delimited but script used space delimiter (cut -d' ')\r\n   - Result: Email field parsing failed, causing garbled data\r\n   \r\n2. BUG 2: Sorting mismatch between users (alphabetical) and emails (numeric by UID)\r\n   - Result: Wrong emails assigned to wrong users due to line number mismatch\r\n   \r\n3. BUG 3: groups.dat is colon-delimited but awk used default space/tab separator\r\n   - Result: Group names not resolved, showing UIDs instead of names\r\n\r\nFIXES APPLIED:\r\n1. Changed email extraction to use awk -F'\\t' (tab delimiter)\r\n2. Removed sorting mismatch by using awk to lookup emails by UID directly\r\n3. Added -F: to all awk commands processing groups.dat\r\n\r\nRESULTS:\r\n- Clean CSV export with 800 users (801 lines including header)\r\n- All fields properly aligned\r\n- Emails correctly matched to users by UID\r\n- Primary and supplementary groups showing names, no"]
[71.045863, "o", "t UIDs\r\n- Output file: /home/user/admin/export.csv (64KB)\r\n\r\nBACKUP:\r\n- Original script backed up to: export_users.sh.backup\r\n"]
